#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:8
msgid "Using SIMD with WebAssembly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:10
msgid ""
"Emscripten supports the `WebAssembly SIMD <https://github.com/webassembly/"
"simd/>`_ feature. There are five different ways to leverage WebAssembly SIMD "
"in your C/C++ programs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:12
msgid ""
"Enable LLVM/Clang SIMD autovectorizer to automatically target WebAssembly "
"SIMD, without requiring changes to C/C++ source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:13
msgid ""
"Write SIMD code using the GCC/Clang SIMD Vector Extensions "
"(``__attribute__((vector_size(16)))``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:14
msgid ""
"Write SIMD code using the WebAssembly SIMD intrinsics (``#include "
"<wasm_simd128.h>``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:15
msgid ""
"Compile existing SIMD code that uses the x86 SSE, SSE2, SSE3, SSSE3, SSE4.1, "
"SSE4.2, AVX or AVX2 intrinsics (``#include <*mmintrin.h>``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:16
msgid ""
"Compile existing SIMD code that uses the ARM NEON intrinsics (``#include "
"<arm_neon.h>``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:18
msgid "These techniques can be freely combined in a single program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:20
msgid ""
"To enable any of the five types of SIMD above, pass the WebAssembly-specific "
"``-msimd128`` flag at compile time. This will also turn on LLVM's "
"autovectorization passes. If that is not desirable, additionally pass flags "
"``-fno-vectorize -fno-slp-vectorize`` to disable the autovectorizer. See "
"`Auto-Vectorization in LLVM <https://llvm.org/docs/Vectorizers.html>`_ for "
"more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:22
msgid "WebAssembly SIMD is supported by"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:24
msgid "Chrome ≥ 91 (May 2021),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:26
msgid "Firefox ≥ 89 (June 2021),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:28
msgid "Safari ≥ 16.4 (March 2023) and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:30
msgid "Node.js ≥ 16.4 (June 2021)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:32
msgid ""
"See `WebAssembly Roadmap <https://webassembly.org/roadmap/>`_ for details "
"about other VMs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:34
msgid ""
"An upcoming `Relaxed SIMD proposal <https://github.com/WebAssembly/relaxed-"
"simd/tree/main/proposals/relaxed-simd>`_ will add more SIMD instructions to "
"WebAssembly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:38
msgid "GCC/Clang SIMD Vector Extensions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:40
msgid ""
"At the source level, the GCC/Clang `SIMD Vector Extensions <https://gcc.gnu."
"org/onlinedocs/gcc/Vector-Extensions.html>`_ can be used and will be lowered "
"to WebAssembly SIMD instructions where possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:42
msgid ""
"This enables developers to create custom wide vector types via typedefs, and "
"use arithmetic operators (+,-,*,/) on the vectorized types, as well as allow "
"individual lane access via the vector[i] notation. However, the `GCC vector "
"built-in functions <https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/x86-Built-in-"
"Functions.html>`_ are not available. Instead, use the WebAssembly SIMD "
"Intrinsics functions below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:46
msgid "WebAssembly SIMD Intrinsics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:48
msgid ""
"LLVM maintains a WebAssembly SIMD Intrinsics header file that is provided "
"with Emscripten, and adds type definitions for the different supported "
"vector types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:69
msgid ""
"The Wasm SIMD header can be browsed online at `wasm_simd128.h <https://"
"github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/main/clang/lib/Headers/wasm_simd128.h>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:71
msgid ""
"Pass flag ``-msimd128`` at compile time to enable targeting WebAssembly SIMD "
"Intrinsics. C/C++ code can use the built-in preprocessor define ``#ifdef "
"__wasm_simd128__`` to detect when building with WebAssembly SIMD enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:73
msgid ""
"Pass ``-mrelaxed-simd`` to target WebAssembly Relaxed SIMD Intrinsics. C/C++ "
"code can use the built-in preprocessor define ``#ifdef "
"__wasm_relaxed_simd__`` to detect when this target is active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:77
msgid "Limitations and behavioral differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:79
msgid ""
"When porting native SIMD code, it should be noted that because of "
"portability concerns, the WebAssembly SIMD specification does not expose "
"access to all of the native x86/ARM SIMD instructions. In particular the "
"following changes exist:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:81
msgid ""
"Emscripten does not support x86 or any other native inline SIMD assembly or "
"building .s assembly files, so all code should be written to use SIMD "
"intrinsic functions or compiler vector extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:83
msgid ""
"WebAssembly SIMD does not have control over managing floating point rounding "
"modes or handling denormals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:85
msgid ""
"Cache line prefetch instructions are not available, and calls to these "
"functions will compile, but are treated as no-ops."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:87
msgid ""
"Asymmetric memory fence operations are not available, but will be "
"implemented as fully synchronous memory fences when SharedArrayBuffer is "
"enabled (-pthread) or as no-ops when multithreading is not enabled (the "
"default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:89
msgid ""
"SIMD-related bug reports are tracked in the `Emscripten bug tracker with the "
"label SIMD <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues?"
"q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3ASIMD>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:93
msgid "Optimization considerations"
msgstr ""

