"When developing SIMD code to use WebAssembly SIMD, implementors should be "
"aware of semantic differences between the host hardware and WebAssembly "
"semantics; as acknowledged in the WebAssembly design documentation, \"`this "
"sometimes will lead to poor performance <https://github.com/WebAssembly/"
"design/blob/master/Portability.md#assumptions-for-efficient-execution>`_.\" "
"The following list outlines some WebAssembly SIMD instructions to look out "
"for when performance tuning:"
msgstr ""

