#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:1236
msgid "Compiling SIMD code targeting ARM NEON instruction set"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:1238
msgid ""
"Emscripten supports compiling existing codebases that use ARM NEON by "
"passing the `-mfpu=neon` directive to the compiler, and including the header "
"`<arm_neon.h>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:1242
msgid ""
"In terms of performance, it is very important to note that only instructions "
"which operate on 128-bit wide vectors are supported cleanly. This means that "
"nearly any instruction which is not of a \"q\" variant (i.e. \"vaddq\" as "
"opposed to \"vadd\") will be scalarized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:1247
msgid ""
"These are pulled from `SIMDe repository on GitHub <https://github.com/simd-"
"everywhere/simde>`_. To update emscripten with the latest SIMDe version, run "
"`tools/simde_update.py`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/simd.rst:1251
